The paper discusses the algebraic properties of traversals of data structures, which are commonly used in programming. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the laws that characterise traversals, which could fall under the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) or Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses containers and their traversal, which could fall under the Computation and Complexity Theory (cs.CC) sub-category.
